1 impose a levy in the same or at a different amount not to
2 exceed two (2) mills, shall be submitted to the resident
3 electors within the proposed district at the first general
4 election held two (2) four (4) years after the election
5 authorizing the district. and every four (4) years
6 thereafter, until defeated. If the proposition to impose or
7 continue a mill levy is defeated, the proposition shall not
8 be submitted to the electors for a period of not less than
9 one (1) year. If the proposition to continue a mill levy
10 under this subsection is approved, the mill levy shall
11 continue until a proposition to rescind the mill levy is
12 submitted to the resident electors of the district and is
13 approved at the next general election after:
